    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I had a pie crust recipe that I adopted as &#8220;my&#8221; pie crust, and swore I&#8217;d never use another. I loved that recipe. It played an integral part in the love story of my husband and me. But then we got married, and somewhere in the midst of planning the wedding, getting married, and moving to Germany, the recipe was left behind in Iowa, and lost forever. I tried others, but nothing could compare. I was heartbroken. In my depression, I resorted to frozen crust. If it wasn&#8217;t my recipe, it wasn&#8217;t worth making, I reasoned. I sadly came to terms with the fact that I may never make another good pie again. Then this recipe came into my life. The addition of the vinegar intrigues me, but more importantly, it has given me hope.</p>
    </div>

