    </div>

      </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-10301" class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Liz</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2008/07/the-important-parts/#comment-10301"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2008-08-13T01:03:00-04:00">Wednesday, August 13, 2008 at 1:03 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Hey Molly, the apricots here are mealy. I tried this recipe with plums yesterday. It was divine, but the bottom crust was sogged out.</></>So today I prebaked it and made it with peaches, which gave off less liquid then the plums. But then again, maybe it just all went into the crust that got soggy.:)</>Whatever, the flavor of the dough is great, and we loved it with ice cream. I can see it with a dry fruit like apples.</p>
    </div>

      </li><!-- #comment-## -->
